Certainly! Below is a JSON representation of the five fundamental objectives of the United Nations:

```json
{
  "UnitedNationsObjectives": [
    {
      "Objective": "Maintain International Peace and Security",
      "Description": "To prevent conflict, help parties in conflict make peace, and create the conditions to allow peace to hold and flourish."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Promote Sustainable Development",
      "Description": "To promote economic growth, social inclusion, environmental sustainability, and good governance for all."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Protect Human Rights",
      "Description": "To uphold international human rights standards and protect individuals from violations."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Uphold International Law",
      "Description": "To promote justice and international law as a means to achieve international peace and security."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Deliver Humanitarian Aid",
      "Description": "To provide relief and recovery assistance to people affected by humanitarian crises."
    }
  ]
}
```

Now, here is a simple JSON parsing example in Python to extract information from this data:

```python
import json

# JSON data as a string
json_data = '''
{
  "UnitedNationsObjectives": [
    {
      "Objective": "Maintain International Peace and Security",
      "Description": "To prevent conflict, help parties in conflict make peace, and create the conditions to allow peace to hold and flourish."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Promote Sustainable Development",
      "Description": "To promote economic growth, social inclusion, environmental sustainability, and good governance for all."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Protect Human Rights",
      "Description": "To uphold international human rights standards and protect individuals from violations."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Uphold International Law",
      "Description": "To promote justice and international law as a means to achieve international peace and security."
    },
    {
      "Objective": "Deliver Humanitarian Aid",
      "Description": "To provide relief and recovery assistance to people affected by humanitarian crises."
    }
  ]
}
'''

# Parse JSON data
data = json.loads(json_data)

# Extract and print each objective and its description
for obj in data['UnitedNationsObjectives']:
    print(f"Objective: {obj['Objective']}")
    print(f"Description: {obj['Description']}")
    print()
```

This code snippet reads the JSON data, parses it, and prints each objective along with its description. You can run this code in any Python environment to see the output.
